    "data_abstract": "CERN-LHC.  Transverse momentum distributions of unidentified primary charged particles are measured for proton-proton collisions at 5.02 and 13 TeV. The distributions are reported for different multiplicity classes defined by either the amplutude in the VZERO forward detector of ALICE or in terms of the track multiplicity at mid-pseudorapidity.\n\nThe average transverse momentum as a function of the mid-pseudorapidity charged particle density is also reported. Events with more than two primary charged particles (transverse momentum above 150 MeV/c) are considered. Results are reported for ten different transverse spherocity classes.",
